Social Welfare Programme for Low-Income Citizens
The UAE's new social welfare programme for low-income citizens targets Emirati families whose total income is less than AED 25,000 a month. The programme covers various social aspects and support schemes packages.
Programme Budget and Management:

Restructured in July 2022 with a budget of AED 28 billion (increased from AED 14 billion)
Managed by Ministry of Community Development (MoCD)
Implemented in September 2022

Three Main Programme Categories:
1. New Allowances:

Unemployed citizens allowance: Up to AED 5,000 per month for citizens over age 45
Housing allowance: Up to AED 2,500 per month
University education allowance: AED 3,200 per month to outstanding students
Unemployed job seekers allowance: AED 5,000 per month for six months

2. Increased Existing Allowances:

Head of family allowance: Increases up to AED 13,000 according to years of experience
Wife allowance: Increases up to AED 3,500 per month
Children allowance:

AED 2,400 per month for the first child
AED 1,600 per month for the second and third child
AED 800 for the fourth child or more



3. Inflation Allowance:

Fuel subsidies: Monthly subsidy of 85% of fuel price increase over AED 2.1 per litre
Electricity and water subsidies: Monthly subsidy of 50% for electricity consumption less than 4,000 kilowatts, and 50% for water consumption less than 26,000 gallons
Food supplements subsidies: 75% of food price inflation

The Social Welfare System
At the federal level, the Ministry of Community Development oversees the UAE's social welfare system. The ministry makes specific allocations to women's organizations to ensure access to economic safety nets and assistance, particularly for women in rural areas.
Legal Provision
According to Federal Law No. 2 of 2001, monthly assistance is provided to the following categories of UAE nationals residing within the UAE:

Disabled or those with special needs
Children whose parents are not known
Emirati women married to expatriates

Eligibility and Value for Social Welfare
General Rule: Only UAE nationals residing in the UAE can avail social assistance from the Ministry of Community Development.
Exceptions for Emirati women married to foreigners:

If husband suffers from disability impairing work ability
If husband is imprisoned for at least two months
If husband is being deported
If husband has no income for reasons beyond his control
If husband's income is less than average family requirements

Other eligible categories:

Emirati widows from marriage to foreigners and their children
Divorcees or widows of Emirati men with children, residing in the country with no income source

Assistance Value:

Decided by UAE Cabinet on recommendation of Minister of Community Development
If beneficiary has other income, assistance is reduced proportionally
Minimum assistance: AED 625 per person

Special Cases

Declined applicants may petition the Minister within 60 days
Assistance cannot be given up or seized (except for court-ordered family support)
Ministry can stop assistance and request reimbursement for false information
Assistance may be paid to legal guardian if beneficiary is unqualified to handle it
Full assistance given to beneficiary's family upon death

Social Welfare Against Disasters
Cabinet Decision No. 22 for 2008 provides monetary compensation to citizens for losses from personal or natural disasters including fire, drowning, and other calamities.
Compensation:

50-80% of total estimated losses in money and properties
Urgent aid including food and shelter immediately after disaster
Emergency cash relief of AED 300 per affected person per day within two days of notification

Regional Programmes
Abu Dhabi Social Support Programme:

Income-based scheme managed by Department of Community Development
Part of Abu Dhabi's 'Ghadan 21' development programme
Available to householders with family book issued by the emirate
Monthly income must be less than approved support line
Application period was from January 6 to March 31, 2019
Apply through UAE Pass on programme website

Social Assistance in Dubai:
Community Development Authority (CDA) offers:

Periodic benefits: For daily living expenses
One-time benefits: Maximum AED 50,000 for medical treatment and education
Emergency benefit: Up to AED 25,000 in cash for emergency situations
Special assistance: Cash for air-conditioners and home furnishing for low-income families

Bunyan Card (Dubai):

Launched by Dubai Municipality for UAE citizens aged 18+
Provides discounts on furniture and building materials
Available at Al Tawar, Al Kafaf, and Hatta centres

Social Assistance in Sharjah:

Social Services Department offers assistance for low-income citizens
Available to those whose income equals or is less than Ministry of Community Development assistance

How to Apply
Eligible individuals can apply for social subsidy services through the Ministry of Community Development website and/or mobile application. Contact MoCD for queries about the programmes.

Economic Enablement programmes:
DGE Gov Academy - Courses and Programs
Executive Education Programs
These programs are tailored for mid-level and senior government managers to build confidence and skills and empower participants to prepare for future challenges through problem-solving and innovative thinking Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement. The programs help participants develop personal and actionable plans to address strategy, organization, and innovation-based opportunities Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement.
Behavioral Competency Programs
These programs help government employees enhance their skills and performance at both personal and institutional levels through general track programs that allow growth in current roles and maximize potential for taking on new responsibilities to support future government needs and functions Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement.
Key objectives include:

Developing employees' capabilities by enhancing their skills to improve overall institutional performance Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement
Exploring various behavioral skills to increase work efficiency and take on new responsibilities to support future government requirements and trends Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement
Building awareness and self-reflection and demonstrating responsibility for self-development and continuous learning Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement
Applying effective communication skills to provide information for others, and influence and inspire them Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement

Specialized Programs
These programs provide unique educational and training opportunities that focus on a wide range of interests and topics, contributing to the enrichment of experiences in Abu Dhabi's public sector and bolstering efforts to build a sustainable knowledge-based economy Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement.
Features include:

Opportunity to earn international accreditations in many fields, such as accounting, digital field, finance, audit, project management, and more Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement
Programs designed for learners passionate about professional career development Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement
Enhancement and sharpening of skills by achieving internal standards in various fields through programs and professional certificates Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement
Acquisition of new skills and tools to be more versatile at current jobs and advance careers Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement

Scholarships and Study Leave Program
This program offers Emirati employees of the Government of Abu Dhabi and candidates from Government entities in the Emirate the opportunity to pursue university studies (Bachelor, Master, PhD), specializing in areas aligned with the priorities and future aspirations of the Government of Abu Dhabi, at leading educational institutions Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement.
Program Details:

Studies can be conducted either inside or outside the country, on a full-time or part-time basis, based on specified selection criteria Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement
Target audience: Abu Dhabi Government employees from the list of Government entities covered by the program Gov Academy - Department of Government Enablement

Training and Development Focus
The Department of Government Enablement is dedicated to enhancing the skills and knowledge of government employees through effective training and development initiatives What we do - Department of Government Enablement.
The Department of Government Enablement facilitates the registration of government employees as learners and maintains accurate records of their course completion, awards, and certifications. It develops assessment strategies, standards, tools, and competency frameworks to evaluate employee capability and manages a dedicated digital platform for conducting assessments of government employees, leaders, and job seekers
